Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm wide wedges, no need to peel) into wedges.

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @chorizo{60%g}(diced) and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.
Bubble until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then transfer to a #bowl{} (keep the pan
- you'll use it again).

Crack the @egg{1} into a medium bowl and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another bowl and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Season the @British chicken breasts{2}, then sandwich each breast between two
pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a
bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Clean out the now empty frying pan back and pop back on high heat. Add enough
oil to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for
> 2-3 minutes before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, and fry until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Once browned, pop the chicken onto another baking tray. Place the chicken on
the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Discard the
> oil from the chicken pan.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{2}(cut into 1cm chunks).

In a medium bowl, combine the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tsp} and
@cider vinegar{15%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir the tomatoes into the dressing, then set aside.

In another bowl, mix together the @creme fraiche{75%g} and
@chipotle paste{20%g}, then set aside.

> Use less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Just before you're ready to serve, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per
person) into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the chicken is ready, cut it into strips. Toss the @pea shoots{40%g} in the
tomato bowl.

Lay the warmed tortillas on your plates, then spread over a spoonful of
chipotle creme fraiche. Top each with some salad, chicken strips and a spoonful
of sweet chilli chorizo - as much as you'd like.

Serve your tacos with the wedges and remaining salad alongside.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!